            <!-- QUESTION 6: DEFENDER - AI Mistakes -->
            <div class="faq-accordion-item">
                <button class="faq-accordion-header">
                    <span>What if the AI makes a mistake on a critical field like a trust account transaction or GL code?</span>
                    <span class="faq-accordion-icon">+</span>
                </button>
                <div class="faq-accordion-content">
                    <p><strong>We build a three-layer validation system to prevent costly errors:</strong></p>
                    <p><strong>Layer 1 - Confidence Scoring:</strong> If the AI's confidence score is below 90% on critical fields (trust account amounts, GL codes, entity allocations), the transaction is automatically flagged for human review.</p>
                    <p><strong>Layer 2 - Business Logic Validation:</strong> We configure rules specific to your requirements. Examples: "Trust deposits must match client matter codes," "Inter-entity loans must balance across entities," "GL codes must exist in chart of accounts." Mismatches trigger alerts.</p>
                    <p><strong>Layer 3 - Human Review Queue:</strong> Flagged transactions route to your senior accountant within the same workflow. Review takes 30-60 seconds to confirm or correct.</p>
                    <p><strong>Target accuracy:</strong> 99%+ on production documents after model training. The small percentage flagged for review prevents catastrophic errors (incorrect trust allocations, wrong entity coding, missed reconciliations).</p>
                    <p>We carry Professional Indemnity insurance. Policy details are provided during the contract phase.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

